10:47 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Mary Anne Cabaluna not in court.  Attorney Mark Stuart Tishberg in court for Mary Anne Cabaluna.  Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Tishberg advises he has not been able to communicate with his client over the last month.  Atty. Tishberg has attempted to call his client multiple times and was possibly hung up on or there was no answer.  Court notes the matter was scheduled for 10:30 a.m. and it is now 10:48 a.m. and the defendant has failed to appear.  State requests a capias be issued and bail be revoked and/or forfeited.  Atty. Tishberg is asking the court to stay a capias and bail forfeiture be stayed to allow him additional time to try to reach out to his client, also noting he may be moving to withdraw as counsel.  Court will deny Atty. Tishberg's request to stay the capias.  Court will issue a capias and orders bail be forfeited.  Atty. Tishberg advises he plans to file a motion to withdraw and asks the matter be set for a hearing date.  Court advises the motion must be filed first before a hearing will be set.  Court will also remove the 11/1/2022 hearing from the calendar as well.
